179 class llvm::AddrLabelMap { ----
180 MCContext &Context; ----
181 struct AddrLabelSymEntry { ----
182 /// The symbols for the label. ----
183 TinyPtrVector Symbols; ----
184 ----
185 Function *Fn; // The containing function of the BasicBlock. ----
186 unsigned Index; // The index in BBCallbacks for the BasicBlock. ----
187 }; ----
188 ----
189 DenseMap, AddrLabelSymEntry> AddrLabelSymbols; ----
190 ----
191 /// Callbacks for the BasicBlock's that we have entries for. We use this so ----
192 /// we get notified if a block is deleted or RAUWd. ----
193 std::vector BBCallbacks; ----
194 ----
195 /// This is a per-function list of symbols whose corresponding BasicBlock got ----
196 /// deleted. These symbols need to be emitted at some point in the file, so ----
197 /// AsmPrinter emits them after the function body. ----
198 DenseMap, std::vector> ----
199 DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission; ----
200 ----
201 public: ----
202 AddrLabelMap(MCContext &context) : Context(context) {} 0
203 ----
204 ~AddrLabelMap() { 0
205 assert(DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.empty() && 0
206 "Some labels for deleted blocks never got emitted"); ----
207 } 0
208 ----
209 ArrayRef getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BasicBlock *BB); ----
210 ----

212 std::vector &Result); ----
213 ----
214 void UpdateForDeletedBlock(BasicBlock *BB); ----
215 void UpdateForRAUWBlock(BasicBlock *Old, BasicBlock *New); ----
216 }; ----

218 ArrayRef AddrLabelMap::getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
219 assert(BB->hasAddressTaken() && 0
220 "Shouldn't get label for block without address taken"); ----
221 AddrLabelSymEntry &Entry = AddrLabelSymbols[BB]; 0
222 ----
223 // If we already had an entry for this block, just return it. ----
224 if (!Entry.Symbols.empty()) { 0
225 assert(BB->getParent() == Entry.Fn && "Parent changed"); 0
226 return Entry.Symbols; 0
227 } ----
228 ----
229 // Otherwise, this is a new entry, create a new symbol for it and add an ----
230 // entry to BBCallbacks so we can be notified if the BB is deleted or RAUWd. ----
231 BBCallbacks.emplace_back(BB); 0
232 BBCallbacks.back().setMap(this); 0
233 Entry.Index = BBCallbacks.size() - 1; 0
234 Entry.Fn = BB->getParent(); 0
235 MCSymbol *Sym = BB->hasAddressTaken() ? Context.createNamedTempSymbol() 0
236 : Context.createTempSymbol(); 0
237 Entry.Symbols.push_back(Sym); 0
238 return Entry.Symbols; 0
239 } ----
240 ----
241 /// If we have any deleted symbols for F, return them. ----
242 void AddrLabelMap::takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction( 0
243 Function *F, std::vector &Result) { ----
244 DenseMap, std::vector>::iterator I = ----
245 DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.find(F); 0
246 ----
247 // If there are no entries for the function, just return. ----
248 if (I == DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.end()) 0
249 return; 0
250 ----
251 // Otherwise, take the list. ----
252 std::swap(Result, I->second); 0
253 DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.erase(I); 0
254 } ----

276 void AddrLabelMap::UpdateForDeletedBlock(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
277 // If the block got deleted, there is no need for the symbol. If the symbol ----
278 // was already emitted, we can just forget about it, otherwise we need to ----
279 // queue it up for later emission when the function is output. ----
280 AddrLabelSymEntry Entry = std::move(AddrLabelSymbols[BB]); 0
281 AddrLabelSymbols.erase(BB); 0
282 assert(!Entry.Symbols.empty() && "Didn't have a symbol, why a callback?"); 0
283 BBCallbacks[Entry.Index] = nullptr; // Clear the callback. 0
284 ----
285 #if !LLVM_MEMORY_SANITIZER_BUILD ----
286 // BasicBlock is destroyed already, so this access is UB detectable by msan. ----
287 assert((BB->getParent() == nullptr || BB->getParent() == Entry.Fn) && 0
288 "Block/parent mismatch"); ----
289 #endif ----
290 ----
291 for (MCSymbol *Sym : Entry.Symbols) { 0
292 if (Sym->isDefined()) 0
293 return; 0
294 ----
295 // If the block is not yet defined, we need to emit it at the end of the ----
296 // function. Add the symbol to the DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission list ----
297 // for the containing Function. Since the block is being deleted, its ----
298 // parent may already be removed, we have to get the function from 'Entry'. ----
299 DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission[Entry.Fn].push_back(Sym); 0
300 } ----
301 } 0
302 ----
303 void AddrLabelMap::UpdateForRAUWBlock(BasicBlock *Old, BasicBlock *New) { 0
304 // Get the entry for the RAUW'd block and remove it from our map. ----
305 AddrLabelSymEntry OldEntry = std::move(AddrLabelSymbols[Old]); 0
306 AddrLabelSymbols.erase(Old); 0
307 assert(!OldEntry.Symbols.empty() && "Didn't have a symbol, why a callback?"); 0
308 ----
309 AddrLabelSymEntry &NewEntry = AddrLabelSymbols[New]; 0
310 ----
311 // If New is not address taken, just move our symbol over to it. ----
312 if (NewEntry.Symbols.empty()) { 0
313 BBCallbacks[OldEntry.Index].setPtr(New); // Update the callback. 0
314 NewEntry = std::move(OldEntry); // Set New's entry. 0
315 return; 0
316 } ----
317 ----
318 BBCallbacks[OldEntry.Index] = nullptr; // Update the callback. 0
319 ----
320 // Otherwise, we need to add the old symbols to the new block's set. ----
321 llvm::append_range(NewEntry.Symbols, OldEntry.Symbols); 0
322 } 0
323 ----
324 void AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr::deleted() { 0
325 Map->UpdateForDeletedBlock(cast(getValPtr())); 0
326 } 0

328 void AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr::allUsesReplacedWith(Value *V2) { 0

330 } 0

673 MCSymbol *AsmPrinter::getSymbolPreferLocal(const GlobalValue &GV) const { 0
674 // On ELF, use .Lfoo$local if GV is a non-interposable GlobalObject with an ----
675 // exact definion (intersection of GlobalValue::hasExactDefinition() and ----
676 // !isInterposable()). These linkages include: external, appending, internal, ----
677 // private. It may be profitable to use a local alias for external. The ----
678 // assembler would otherwise be conservative and assume a global default ----
679 // visibility symbol can be interposable, even if the code generator already ----
680 // assumed it. ----
681 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() && GV.canBenefitFromLocalAlias()) { 0
682 const Module &M = *GV.getParent(); 0
683 if (TM.getRelocationModel() != Reloc::Static && 0
684 M.getPIELevel() == PIELevel::Default && GV.isDSOLocal()) 0
685 return getSymbolWithGlobalValueBase(&GV, "$local"); 0
686 } ----
687 return TM.getSymbol(&GV); 0
688 } ----

690 /// EmitGlobalVariable - Emit the specified global variable to the .s file. ----
691 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
692 bool IsEmuTLSVar = TM.useEmulatedTLS() && GV->isThreadLocal(); 0
693 assert(!(IsEmuTLSVar && GV->hasCommonLinkage()) && 0
694 "No emulated TLS variables in the common section"); ----
695 ----
696 // Never emit TLS variable xyz in emulated TLS model. ----
697 // The initialization value is in __emutls_t.xyz instead of xyz. ----
698 if (IsEmuTLSVar) 0
699 return; 0
700 ----
701 if (GV->hasInitializer()) { 0
702 // Check to see if this is a special global used by LLVM, if so, emit it. ----
703 if (emitSpecialLLVMGlobal(GV)) 0
704 return; 0
705 ----
706 // Skip the emission of global equivalents. The symbol can be emitted later ----
707 // on by emitGlobalGOTEquivs in case it turns out to be needed. ----
708 if (GlobalGOTEquivs.count(getSymbol(GV))) 0
709 return; 0
710 ----
711 if (isVerbose()) { 0
712 // When printing the control variable __emutls_v.*, ----
713 // we don't need to print the original TLS variable name. ----
714 GV->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->getCommentOS(), 0
715 /*PrintType=*/false, GV->getParent()); ----
716 OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << '\n'; 0
717 } ----
718 } ----
719 ----
720 MCSymbol *GVSym = getSymbol(GV); 0
721 MCSymbol *EmittedSym = GVSym; 0
722 ----
723 // getOrCreateEmuTLSControlSym only creates the symbol with name and default ----
724 // attributes. ----
725 // GV's or GVSym's attributes will be used for the EmittedSym. ----
726 emitVisibility(EmittedSym, GV->getVisibility(), !GV->isDeclaration()); 0
727 ----
728 if (GV->isTagged()) { 0
729 Triple T = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
730 ----
731 if (T.getArch() != Triple::aarch64 || !T.isAndroid()) 0
732 OutContext.reportError(SMLoc(), 0

734 "only supported on AArch64 Android"); ----
735 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(EmittedSym, MAI->getMemtagAttr()); 0
736 } 0
737 ----
738 if (!GV->hasInitializer()) // External globals require no extra code. 0
739 return; 0
740 ----
741 GVSym->redefineIfPossible(); 0
742 if (GVSym->isDefined() || GVSym->isVariable()) 0

744 "' is already defined"); 0

748 ----
749 SectionKind GVKind = TargetLoweringObjectFile::getKindForGlobal(GV, TM); 0
750 ----
751 const DataLayout &DL = GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
752 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GV->getValueType()); 0
753 ----
754 // If the alignment is specified, we *must* obey it. Overaligning a global ----
755 // with a specified alignment is a prompt way to break globals emitted to ----
756 // sections and expected to be contiguous (e.g. ObjC metadata). ----
757 const Align Alignment = getGVAlignment(GV, DL); 0
758 ----
759 for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) { 0
760 NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, ----
761 HI.TimerGroupName, HI.TimerGroupDescription, ----
762 TimePassesIsEnabled); 0
763 HI.Handler->setSymbolSize(GVSym, Size); 0
764 } 0
765 ----
766 // Handle common symbols ----
767 if (GVKind.isCommon()) { 0
768 if (Size == 0) Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it. 0
769 // .comm _foo, 42, 4 ----
770 OutStreamer->emitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment); 0
771 return; 0
772 } ----
773 ----
774 // Determine to which section this global should be emitted. ----
775 MCSection *TheSection = getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(GV, GVKind, TM); 0
776 ----
777 // If we have a bss global going to a section that supports the ----
778 // zerofill directive, do so here. ----
779 if (GVKind.isBSS() && MAI->hasMachoZeroFillDirective() && 0
780 TheSection->isVirtualSection()) { 0
781 if (Size == 0) 0
782 Size = 1; // zerofill of 0 bytes is undefined. 0
783 emitLinkage(GV, GVSym); 0
784 // .zerofill __DATA, __bss, _foo, 400, 5 ----
785 OutStreamer->emitZerofill(TheSection, GVSym, Size, Alignment); 0
786 return; 0
787 } ----
788 ----
789 // If this is a BSS local symbol and we are emitting in the BSS ----
790 // section use .lcomm/.comm directive. ----
791 if (GVKind.isBSSLocal() && 0
792 getObjFileLowering().getBSSSection() == TheSection) { 0
793 if (Size == 0) 0
794 Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it. 0
795 ----
796 // Use .lcomm only if it supports user-specified alignment. ----
797 // Otherwise, while it would still be correct to use .lcomm in some ----
798 // cases (e.g. when Align == 1), the external assembler might enfore ----
799 // some -unknown- default alignment behavior, which could cause ----
800 // spurious differences between external and integrated assembler. ----
801 // Prefer to simply fall back to .local / .comm in this case. ----
802 if (MAI->getLCOMMDirectiveAlignmentType() != LCOMM::NoAlignment) { 0
803 // .lcomm _foo, 42 ----
804 OutStreamer->emitLocalCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment); 0
805 return; 0
806 } ----
807 ----
808 // .local _foo ----
809 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Local); 0
810 // .comm _foo, 42, 4 ----
811 OutStreamer->emitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment); 0
812 return; 0
813 } ----
814 ----
815 // Handle thread local data for mach-o which requires us to output an ----
816 // additional structure of data and mangle the original symbol so that we ----
817 // can reference it later. ----
818 // ----
819 // TODO: This should become an "emit thread local global" method on TLOF. ----
820 // All of this macho specific stuff should be sunk down into TLOFMachO and ----
821 // stuff like "TLSExtraDataSection" should no longer be part of the parent ----
822 // TLOF class. This will also make it more obvious that stuff like ----
823 // MCStreamer::EmitTBSSSymbol is macho specific and only called from macho ----
824 // specific code. ----
825 if (GVKind.isThreadLocal() && MAI->hasMachoTBSSDirective()) { 0
826 // Emit the .tbss symbol ----
827 MCSymbol *MangSym = ----
828 OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(GVSym->getName() + Twine("$tlv$init")); 0
829 ----
830 if (GVKind.isThreadBSS()) { 0
831 TheSection = getObjFileLowering().getTLSBSSSection(); 0
832 OutStreamer->emitTBSSSymbol(TheSection, MangSym, Size, Alignment); 0
833 } else if (GVKind.isThreadData()) { 0
834 OutStreamer->switchSection(TheSection); 0
835 ----
836 emitAlignment(Alignment, GV); 0
837 OutStreamer->emitLabel(MangSym); 0
838 ----
839 emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), 0
840 GV->getInitializer()); ----
841 } ----
842 ----
843 OutStreamer->addBlankLine(); 0
844 ----
845 // Emit the variable struct for the runtime. ----
846 MCSection *TLVSect = getObjFileLowering().getTLSExtraDataSection(); 0
847 ----
848 OutStreamer->switchSection(TLVSect); 0
849 // Emit the linkage here. ----
850 emitLinkage(GV, GVSym); 0
851 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GVSym); 0
852 ----
853 // Three pointers in size: ----
854 // - __tlv_bootstrap - used to make sure support exists ----
855 // - spare pointer, used when mapped by the runtime ----
856 // - pointer to mangled symbol above with initializer ----
857 unsigned PtrSize = DL.getPointerTypeSize(GV->getType()); 0
858 OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(GetExternalSymbolSymbol("_tlv_bootstrap"), 0
859 PtrSize); ----
860 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PtrSize); 0
861 OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(MangSym, PtrSize); 0
862 ----
863 OutStreamer->addBlankLine(); 0
864 return; 0
865 } ----
866 ----
867 MCSymbol *EmittedInitSym = GVSym; 0
868 ----
869 OutStreamer->switchSection(TheSection); 0
870 ----
871 emitLinkage(GV, EmittedInitSym); 0
872 emitAlignment(Alignment, GV); 0
873 ----
874 OutStreamer->emitLabel(EmittedInitSym); 0
875 MCSymbol *LocalAlias = getSymbolPreferLocal(*GV); 0
876 if (LocalAlias != EmittedInitSym) 0
877 OutStreamer->emitLabel(LocalAlias); 0
878 ----
879 emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer()); 0
880 ----
881 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective()) 0
882 // .size foo, 42 ----
883 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(EmittedInitSym, 0
884 MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext)); 0
885 ----
886 OutStreamer->addBlankLine(); 0
887 } ----

1133 /// emitDebugValueComment - This method handles the target-independent form ----
1134 /// of DBG_VALUE, returning true if it was able to do so. A false return ----
1135 /// means the target will need to handle MI in EmitInstruction. ----
1136 static bool emitDebugValueComment(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) { 0
1137 // This code handles only the 4-operand target-independent form. ----
1138 if (MI->isNonListDebugValue() && MI->getNumOperands() != 4) 0
1139 return false; 0
1140 ----
1141 SmallString<128> Str; 0
1142 raw_svector_ostream OS(Str); 0
1143 OS << "DEBUG_VALUE: "; 0
1144 ----
1145 const DILocalVariable *V = MI->getDebugVariable(); 0
1146 if (auto *SP = dyn_cast(V->getScope())) { 0
1147 StringRef Name = SP->getName(); 0
1148 if (!Name.empty()) 0
1149 OS << Name << ":"; 0
1150 } ----
1151 OS << V->getName(); 0
1152 OS << " <- "; 0
1153 ----
1154 const DIExpression *Expr = MI->getDebugExpression(); 0
1155 // First convert this to a non-variadic expression if possible, to simplify ----
1156 // the output. ----
1157 if (auto NonVariadicExpr = DIExpression::convertToNonVariadicExpression(Expr)) 0
1158 Expr = *NonVariadicExpr; 0
1159 // Then, output the possibly-simplified expression. ----
1160 if (Expr->getNumElements()) { 0
1161 OS << '['; 0
1162 ListSeparator LS; 0
1163 for (auto &Op : Expr->expr_ops()) { 0
1164 OS << LS << dwarf::OperationEncodingString(Op.getOp()); 0
1165 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Op.getNumArgs(); ++I) 0
1166 OS << ' ' << Op.getArg(I); 0
1167 } ----
1168 OS << "] "; 0
1169 } ----
1170 ----
1171 // Register or immediate value. Register 0 means undef. ----
1172 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->debug_operands()) { 0
1173 if (&Op != MI->debug_operands().begin()) 0
1174 OS << ", "; 0
1175 switch (Op.getType()) { 0
1176 case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: { 0
1177 APFloat APF = APFloat(Op.getFPImm()->getValueAPF()); 0
1178 Type *ImmTy = Op.getFPImm()->getType(); 0
1179 if (ImmTy->isBFloatTy() || ImmTy->isHalfTy() || ImmTy->isFloatTy() || 0
1180 ImmTy->isDoubleTy()) { 0
1181 OS << APF.convertToDouble(); 0
1182 } else { ----
1183 // There is no good way to print long double. Convert a copy to ----
1184 // double. Ah well, it's only a comment. ----
1185 bool ignored; ----
1186 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, 0
1187 &ignored); ----
1188 OS << "(long double) " << APF.convertToDouble(); 0
1189 } ----
1190 break; 0
1191 } 0
1192 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
1193 OS << Op.getImm(); 0
1194 break; 0
1195 } ----
1196 case MachineOperand::MO_CImmediate: { 0
1197 Op.getCImm()->getValue().print(OS, false /*isSigned*/); 0
1198 break; 0
1199 } ----
1200 case MachineOperand::MO_TargetIndex: { 0
1201 OS << "!target-index(" << Op.getIndex() << "," << Op.getOffset() << ")"; 0
1202 break; 0
1203 } ----
1204 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: 0
1205 case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex: { ----
1206 Register Reg; 0
1207 std::optional Offset; 0
1208 if (Op.isReg()) { 0
1209 Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
1210 } else { ----
1211 const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = ----
1212 AP.MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering(); 0
1213 Offset = TFI->getFrameIndexReference(*AP.MF, Op.getIndex(), Reg); 0
1214 } ----
1215 if (!Reg) { 0
1216 // Suppress offset, it is not meaningful here. ----
1217 OS << "undef"; 0
1218 break; 0
1219 } ----
1220 // The second operand is only an offset if it's an immediate. ----
1221 if (MI->isIndirectDebugValue()) 0
1222 Offset = StackOffset::getFixed(MI->getDebugOffset().getImm()); 0
1223 if (Offset) 0
1224 OS << '['; 0
1225 OS << printReg(Reg, AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo()); 0
1226 if (Offset) 0
1227 OS << '+' << Offset->getFixed() << ']'; 0
1228 break; 0
1229 } ----
1230 default: 0
1231 llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type"); 0
1232 } ----
1233 } ----
1234 ----
1235 // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment. ----
1236 AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str()); 0
1237 return true; 0
1238 } 0

1334 /// Returns the BB metadata to be emitted in the SHT_LLVM_BB_ADDR_MAP section ----
1335 /// for a given basic block. This can be used to capture more precise profile ----
1336 /// information. ----
1337 static uint32_t getBBAddrMapMetadata(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1338 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
1339 return object::BBAddrMap::BBEntry::Metadata{ 0
1340 MBB.isReturnBlock(), !MBB.empty() && TII->isTailCall(MBB.back()), 0
1341 MBB.isEHPad(), const_cast(MBB).canFallThrough(), 0
1342 !MBB.empty() && MBB.rbegin()->isIndirectBranch()} 0
1343 .encode(); 0

1345 ----
1346 void AsmPrinter::emitBBAddrMapSection(const MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1347 MCSection *BBAddrMapSection = ----
1348 getObjFileLowering().getBBAddrMapSection(*MF.getSection()); 0
1349 assert(BBAddrMapSection && ".llvm_bb_addr_map section is not initialized."); 0
1350 ----
1351 const MCSymbol *FunctionSymbol = getFunctionBegin(); 0
1352 ----
1353 OutStreamer->pushSection(); 0
1354 OutStreamer->switchSection(BBAddrMapSection); 0
1355 OutStreamer->AddComment("version"); 0
1356 uint8_t BBAddrMapVersion = OutStreamer->getContext().getBBAddrMapVersion(); 0
1357 OutStreamer->emitInt8(BBAddrMapVersion); 0
1358 OutStreamer->AddComment("feature"); 0
1359 OutStreamer->emitInt8(0); 0
1360 OutStreamer->AddComment("function address"); 0
1361 OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(FunctionSymbol, getPointerSize()); 0
1362 OutStreamer->AddComment("number of basic blocks"); 0
1363 OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(MF.size()); 0
1364 const MCSymbol *PrevMBBEndSymbol = FunctionSymbol; 0
1365 // Emit BB Information for each basic block in the function. ----
1366 for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1367 const MCSymbol *MBBSymbol = ----
1368 MBB.isEntryBlock() ? FunctionSymbol : MBB.getSymbol(); 0
1369 // TODO: Remove this check when version 1 is deprecated. ----
1370 if (BBAddrMapVersion > 1) { 0
1371 OutStreamer->AddComment("BB id"); 0
1372 // Emit the BB ID for this basic block. ----
1373 OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(*MBB.getBBID()); 0
1374 } ----
1375 // Emit the basic block offset relative to the end of the previous block. ----
1376 // This is zero unless the block is padded due to alignment. ----
1377 emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(MBBSymbol, PrevMBBEndSymbol); 0
1378 // Emit the basic block size. When BBs have alignments, their size cannot ----
1379 // always be computed from their offsets. ----
1380 emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(MBB.getEndSymbol(), MBBSymbol); 0
1381 // Emit the Metadata. ----
1382 OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(getBBAddrMapMetadata(MBB)); 0
1383 PrevMBBEndSymbol = MBB.getEndSymbol(); 0
1384 } ----
1385 OutStreamer->popSection(); 0
1386 } 0
1387 ----
1388 void AsmPrinter::emitKCFITrapEntry(const MachineFunction &MF, 0
1389 const MCSymbol *Symbol) { ----
1390 MCSection *Section = ----
1391 getObjFileLowering().getKCFITrapSection(*MF.getSection()); 0
1392 if (!Section) 0

1394 ----
1395 OutStreamer->pushSection(); 0

1400 OutStreamer->emitAbsoluteSymbolDiff(Symbol, Loc, 4); 0
1401 ----
1402 OutStreamer->popSection(); 0

1488 void AsmPrinter::emitPCSections(const MachineFunction &MF) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1489 const Function &F = MF.getFunction(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1490 if (PCSectionsSymbols.empty() && !F.hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections)) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1491 return; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1492 ----
1493 const CodeModel::Model CM = MF.getTarget().getCodeModel(); 0
1494 const unsigned RelativeRelocSize = ----
1495 (CM == CodeModel::Medium || CM == CodeModel::Large) ? getPointerSize() 0
1496 : 4; 0
1497 ----
1498 // Switch to PCSection, short-circuiting the common case where the current ----
1499 // section is still valid (assume most MD_pcsections contain just 1 section). ----
1500 auto SwitchSection = [&, Prev = StringRef()](const StringRef &Sec) mutable { 0
1501 if (Sec == Prev) 0
1502 return; 0
1503 MCSection *S = getObjFileLowering().getPCSection(Sec, MF.getSection()); 0
1504 assert(S && "PC section is not initialized"); 0
1505 OutStreamer->switchSection(S); 0
1506 Prev = Sec; 0
1507 }; 0
1508 // Emit symbols into sections and data as specified in the pcsections MDNode. ----
1509 auto EmitForMD = [&](const MDNode &MD, ArrayRef Syms, 0
1510 bool Deltas) { ----
1511 // Expect the first operand to be a section name. After that, a tuple of ----
1512 // constants may appear, which will simply be emitted into the current ----
1513 // section (the user of MD_pcsections decides the format of encoded data). ----
1514 assert(isa(MD.getOperand(0)) && "first operand not a string"); 0
1515 bool ConstULEB128 = false; 0
1516 for (const MDOperand &MDO : MD.operands()) { 0
1517 if (auto *S = dyn_cast(MDO)) { 0
1518 // Found string, start of new section! ----
1519 // Find options for this section "
!" - supported options:
 ----
1520 // C = Compress constant integers of size 2-8 bytes as ULEB128. ----
1521 const StringRef SecWithOpt = S->getString(); 0
1522 const size_t OptStart = SecWithOpt.find('!'); // likely npos 0
1523 const StringRef Sec = SecWithOpt.substr(0, OptStart); 0
1524 const StringRef Opts = SecWithOpt.substr(OptStart); // likely empty 0
1525 ConstULEB128 = Opts.find('C') != StringRef::npos; 0
1526 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1527 for (char O : Opts) 0
1528 assert((O == '!' || O == 'C') && "Invalid !pcsections options"); 0
1529 #endif ----
1530 SwitchSection(Sec); 0
1531 const MCSymbol *Prev = Syms.front(); 0
1532 for (const MCSymbol *Sym : Syms) { 0
1533 if (Sym == Prev || !Deltas) { 0
1534 // Use the entry itself as the base of the relative offset. ----
1535 MCSymbol *Base = MF.getContext().createTempSymbol("pcsection_base"); 0
1536 OutStreamer->emitLabel(Base); 0
1537 // Emit relative relocation `addr - base`, which avoids a dynamic ----
1538 // relocation in the final binary. User will get the address with ----
1539 // `base + addr`. ----
1540 emitLabelDifference(Sym, Base, RelativeRelocSize); 0
1541 } else { 0
1542 // Emit delta between symbol and previous symbol. ----
1543 if (ConstULEB128) 0
1544 emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(Sym, Prev); 0
1545 else ----
1546 emitLabelDifference(Sym, Prev, 4); 0
1547 } ----
1548 Prev = Sym; 0
1549 } ----
1550 } else { ----
1551 // Emit auxiliary data after PC. ----
1552 assert(isa(MDO) && "expecting either string or tuple"); 0
1553 const auto *AuxMDs = cast(MDO); 0
1554 for (const MDOperand &AuxMDO : AuxMDs->operands()) { 0
1555 assert(isa(AuxMDO) && "expecting a constant"); 0
1556 const Constant *C = cast(AuxMDO)->getValue(); 0
1557 const DataLayout &DL = F.getParent()->getDataLayout(); 0
1558 const uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeStoreSize(C->getType()); 0
1559 ----
1560 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast(C); 0
1561 CI && ConstULEB128 && Size > 1 && Size <= 8) { 0
1562 emitULEB128(CI->getZExtValue()); 0
1563 } else { ----
1564 emitGlobalConstant(DL, C); 0
1565 } ----
1566 } ----
1567 } ----
1568 } ----
1569 }; 0
1570 ----
1571 OutStreamer->pushSection(); 0
1572 // Emit PCs for function start and function size. ----
1573 if (const MDNode *MD = F.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections)) 0
1574 EmitForMD(*MD, {getFunctionBegin(), getFunctionEnd()}, true); 0
1575 // Emit PCs for instructions collected. ----
1576 for (const auto &MS : PCSectionsSymbols) 0
1577 EmitForMD(*MS.first, MS.second, false); 0
1578 OutStreamer->popSection(); 0
1579 PCSectionsSymbols.clear(); 0
1580 } ----
1581 ----

1584 MachineModuleInfo &MMI = MF.getMMI(); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1585 if (!MF.getLandingPads().empty() || MF.hasEHFunclets() || 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1586 MMI.hasDebugInfo() || 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1587 MF.getFunction().hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections)) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1588 return true; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll

1942 /// Compute the number of Global Variables that uses a Constant. ----
1943 static unsigned getNumGlobalVariableUses(const Constant *C) { 0
1944 if (!C) 0
1945 return 0; 0
1946 ----
1947 if (isa(C)) 0
1948 return 1; 0
1949 ----
1950 unsigned NumUses = 0; 0
1951 for (const auto *CU : C->users()) 0
1952 NumUses += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast(CU)); 0
1953 ----
1954 return NumUses; 0
1955 } ----
1956 ----
1957 /// Only consider global GOT equivalents if at least one user is a ----
1958 /// cstexpr inside an initializer of another global variables. Also, don't ----
1959 /// handle cstexpr inside instructions. During global variable emission, ----
1960 /// candidates are skipped and are emitted later in case at least one cstexpr ----
1961 /// isn't replaced by a PC relative GOT entry access. ----
1962 static bool isGOTEquivalentCandidate(const GlobalVariable *GV, 0
1963 unsigned &NumGOTEquivUsers) { ----
1964 // Global GOT equivalents are unnamed private globals with a constant ----
1965 // pointer initializer to another global symbol. They must point to a ----
1966 // GlobalVariable or Function, i.e., as GlobalValue. ----
1967 if (!GV->hasGlobalUnnamedAddr() || !GV->hasInitializer() || 0
1968 !GV->isConstant() || !GV->isDiscardableIfUnused() || 0
1969 !isa(GV->getOperand(0))) 0
1970 return false; 0
1971 ----
1972 // To be a got equivalent, at least one of its users need to be a constant ----
1973 // expression used by another global variable. ----
1974 for (const auto *U : GV->users()) 0
1975 NumGOTEquivUsers += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast(U)); 0
1976 ----
1977 return NumGOTEquivUsers > 0; 0
1978 } ----
1979 ----
1980 /// Unnamed constant global variables solely contaning a pointer to ----
1981 /// another globals variable is equivalent to a GOT table entry; it contains the ----
1982 /// the address of another symbol. Optimize it and replace accesses to these ----
1983 /// "GOT equivalents" by using the GOT entry for the final global instead. ----
1984 /// Compute GOT equivalent candidates among all global variables to avoid ----
1985 /// emitting them if possible later on, after it use is replaced by a GOT entry ----
1986 /// access. ----
1987 void AsmPrinter::computeGlobalGOTEquivs(Module &M) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1988 if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1989 return; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1990 ----
1991 for (const auto &G : M.globals()) { 0
1992 unsigned NumGOTEquivUsers = 0; 0
1993 if (!isGOTEquivalentCandidate(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers)) 0
1994 continue; 0
1995 ----
1996 const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = getSymbol(&G); 0
1997 GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers); 0
1998 } ----
1999 } ----
2000 ----
2001 /// Constant expressions using GOT equivalent globals may not be eligible ----
2002 /// for PC relative GOT entry conversion, in such cases we need to emit such ----
2003 /// globals we previously omitted in EmitGlobalVariable. ----
2004 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalGOTEquivs() { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2005 if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2006 return; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2007 ----
2008 SmallVector FailedCandidates; 0
2009 for (auto &I : GlobalGOTEquivs) { 0
2010 const GlobalVariable *GV = I.second.first; 0
2011 unsigned Cnt = I.second.second; 0
2012 if (Cnt) 0
2013 FailedCandidates.push_back(GV); 0
2014 } ----
2015 GlobalGOTEquivs.clear(); 0
2016 ----
2017 for (const auto *GV : FailedCandidates) 0
2018 emitGlobalVariable(GV); 0
2019 } 0

2021 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalAlias(Module &M, const GlobalAlias &GA) { 0
2022 MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&GA); 0
2023 bool IsFunction = GA.getValueType()->isFunctionTy(); 0
2024 // Treat bitcasts of functions as functions also. This is important at least ----
2025 // on WebAssembly where object and function addresses can't alias each other. ----
2026 if (!IsFunction) 0
2027 IsFunction = isa(GA.getAliasee()->stripPointerCasts()); 0
2028 ----
2029 // AIX's assembly directive `.set` is not usable for aliasing purpose, ----
2030 // so AIX has to use the extra-label-at-definition strategy. At this ----
2031 // point, all the extra label is emitted, we just have to emit linkage for ----
2032 // those labels. ----
2033 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatXCOFF()) { 0
2034 assert(MAI->hasVisibilityOnlyWithLinkage() && 0
2035 "Visibility should be handled with emitLinkage() on AIX."); ----
2036 ----
2037 // Linkage for alias of global variable has been emitted. ----
2038 if (isa(GA.getAliaseeObject())) 0
2039 return; 0
2040 ----
2041 emitLinkage(&GA, Name); 0
2042 // If it's a function, also emit linkage for aliases of function entry ----
2043 // point. ----
2044 if (IsFunction) 0
2045 emitLinkage(&GA, 0
2046 getObjFileLowering().getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(&GA, TM)); 0
2047 return; 0
2048 } ----
2049 ----
2050 if (GA.hasExternalLinkage() || !MAI->getWeakRefDirective()) 0
2051 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_Global); 0
2052 else if (GA.hasWeakLinkage() || GA.hasLinkOnceLinkage()) 0
2053 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_WeakReference); 0
2054 else ----
2055 assert(GA.hasLocalLinkage() && "Invalid alias linkage"); 0
2056 ----
2057 // Set the symbol type to function if the alias has a function type. ----
2058 // This affects codegen when the aliasee is not a function. ----
2059 if (IsFunction) { 0
2060 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction); 0
2061 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) { 0
2062 OutStreamer->beginCOFFSymbolDef(Name); 0
2063 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolStorageClass( 0
2064 GA.hasLocalLinkage() ? COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_STATIC 0
2065 : COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_EXTERNAL); ----
2066 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolType(COFF::IMAGE_SYM_DTYPE_FUNCTION 0
2067 << COFF::SCT_COMPLEX_TYPE_SHIFT); ----
2068 OutStreamer->endCOFFSymbolDef(); 0
2069 } ----
2070 } ----
2071 ----
2072 emitVisibility(Name, GA.getVisibility()); 0
2073 ----
2074 const MCExpr *Expr = lowerConstant(GA.getAliasee()); 0
2075 ----
2076 if (MAI->hasAltEntry() && isa(Expr)) 0
2077 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_AltEntry); 0
2078 ----
2079 // Emit the directives as assignments aka .set: ----
2080 OutStreamer->emitAssignment(Name, Expr); 0
2081 MCSymbol *LocalAlias = getSymbolPreferLocal(GA); 0
2082 if (LocalAlias != Name) 0
2083 OutStreamer->emitAssignment(LocalAlias, Expr); 0
2084 ----
2085 // If the aliasee does not correspond to a symbol in the output, i.e. the ----
2086 // alias is not of an object or the aliased object is private, then set the ----
2087 // size of the alias symbol from the type of the alias. We don't do this in ----
2088 // other situations as the alias and aliasee having differing types but same ----
2089 // size may be intentional. ----
2090 const GlobalObject *BaseObject = GA.getAliaseeObject(); 0
2091 if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective() && GA.getValueType()->isSized() && 0
2092 (!BaseObject || BaseObject->hasPrivateLinkage())) { 0
2093 const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout(); 0
2094 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GA.getValueType()); 0
2095 OutStreamer->emitELFSize(Name, MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext)); 0
2096 } ----
2097 } ----

2463 // Keep track the alignment, constpool entries per Section. ----
2464 struct SectionCPs { ----
2465 MCSection *S; ----
2466 Align Alignment; ----
2467 SmallVector CPEs; ----
2468 ----
2469 SectionCPs(MCSection *s, Align a) : S(s), Alignment(a) {} 0
2470 }; ----

2474 /// EmitConstantPool - Print to the current output stream assembly ----
2475 /// representations of the constants in the constant pool MCP. This is ----
2476 /// used to print out constants which have been "spilled to memory" by ----
2477 /// the code generator. ----
2478 void AsmPrinter::emitConstantPool() { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2479 const MachineConstantPool *MCP = MF->getConstantPool(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2480 const std::vector &CP = MCP->getConstants(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2481 if (CP.empty()) return; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2482 ----
2483 // Calculate sections for constant pool entries. We collect entries to go into ----
2484 // the same section together to reduce amount of section switch statements. ----
2485 SmallVector CPSections; 0
2486 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CP.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2487 const MachineConstantPoolEntry &CPE = CP[i]; 0
2488 Align Alignment = CPE.getAlign(); 0
2489 ----
2490 SectionKind Kind = CPE.getSectionKind(&getDataLayout()); 0
2491 ----
2492 const Constant *C = nullptr; 0
2493 if (!CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry()) 0
2494 C = CPE.Val.ConstVal; 0
2495 ----
2496 MCSection *S = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForConstant( 0
2497 getDataLayout(), Kind, C, Alignment); ----
2498 ----
2499 // The number of sections are small, just do a linear search from the ----
2500 // last section to the first. ----
2501 bool Found = false; 0
2502 unsigned SecIdx = CPSections.size(); 0
2503 while (SecIdx != 0) { 0
2504 if (CPSections[--SecIdx].S == S) { 0
2505 Found = true; 0
2506 break; 0
2507 } ----
2508 } ----
2509 if (!Found) { 0
2510 SecIdx = CPSections.size(); 0
2511 CPSections.push_back(SectionCPs(S, Alignment)); 0
2512 } ----
2513 ----
2514 if (Alignment > CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment) 0
2515 CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment = Alignment; 0
2516 CPSections[SecIdx].CPEs.push_back(i); 0
2517 } ----
2518 ----
2519 // Now print stuff into the calculated sections. ----
2520 const MCSection *CurSection = nullptr; 0
2521 unsigned Offset = 0; 0
2522 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPSections.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2523 for (unsigned j = 0, ee = CPSections[i].CPEs.size(); j != ee; ++j) { 0
2524 unsigned CPI = CPSections[i].CPEs[j]; 0
2525 MCSymbol *Sym = GetCPISymbol(CPI); 0
2526 if (!Sym->isUndefined()) 0
2527 continue; 0
2528 ----
2529 if (CurSection != CPSections[i].S) { 0
2530 OutStreamer->switchSection(CPSections[i].S); 0
2531 emitAlignment(Align(CPSections[i].Alignment)); 0
2532 CurSection = CPSections[i].S; 0
2533 Offset = 0; 0
2534 } ----
2535 ----
2536 MachineConstantPoolEntry CPE = CP[CPI]; 0
2537 ----
2538 // Emit inter-object padding for alignment. ----
2539 unsigned NewOffset = alignTo(Offset, CPE.getAlign()); 0
2540 OutStreamer->emitZeros(NewOffset - Offset); 0
2541 ----
2542 Offset = NewOffset + CPE.getSizeInBytes(getDataLayout()); 0
2543 ----
2544 OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym); 0
2545 if (CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry()) 0
2546 emitMachineConstantPoolValue(CPE.Val.MachineCPVal); 0
2547 else ----
2548 emitGlobalConstant(getDataLayout(), CPE.Val.ConstVal); 0
2549 } ----
2550 } ----
2551 } 0

2553 // Print assembly representations of the jump tables used by the current ----
2554 // function. ----
2555 void AsmPrinter::emitJumpTableInfo() { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2556 const DataLayout &DL = MF->getDataLayout(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2557 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2558 if (!MJTI) return; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2559 if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline) return; 0
2560 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
2561 if (JT.empty()) return; 0
2562 ----
2563 // Pick the directive to use to print the jump table entries, and switch to ----
2564 // the appropriate section. ----
2565 const Function &F = MF->getFunction(); 0
2566 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering(); 0
2567 bool JTInDiffSection = !TLOF.shouldPutJumpTableInFunctionSection( 0
2568 MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32, 0
2569 F); 0
2570 if (JTInDiffSection) { 0
2571 // Drop it in the readonly section. ----
2572 MCSection *ReadOnlySection = TLOF.getSectionForJumpTable(F, TM); 0
2573 OutStreamer->switchSection(ReadOnlySection); 0
2574 } ----
2575 ----
2576 emitAlignment(Align(MJTI->getEntryAlignment(DL))); 0
2577 ----
2578 // Jump tables in code sections are marked with a data_region directive ----
2579 // where that's supported. ----
2580 if (!JTInDiffSection) 0
2581 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionJT32); 0
2582 ----
2583 for (unsigned JTI = 0, e = JT.size(); JTI != e; ++JTI) { 0
2584 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
2585 ----
2586 // If this jump table was deleted, ignore it. ----
2587 if (JTBBs.empty()) continue; 0
2588 ----
2589 // For the EK_LabelDifference32 entry, if using .set avoids a relocation, ----
2590 /// emit a .set directive for each unique entry. ----
2591 if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32 && 0
2592 MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) { 0
2593 SmallPtrSet EmittedSets; 0
2594 const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2595 const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF,JTI,OutContext); 0
2596 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs) { 0
2597 if (!EmittedSets.insert(MBB).second) 0
2598 continue; 0
2599 ----
2600 // .set LJTSet, LBB32-base ----
2601 const MCExpr *LHS = ----
2602 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
2603 OutStreamer->emitAssignment(GetJTSetSymbol(JTI, MBB->getNumber()), 0
2604 MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, Base, 0
2605 OutContext)); ----
2606 } ----
2607 } 0
2608 ----
2609 // On some targets (e.g. Darwin) we want to emit two consecutive labels ----
2610 // before each jump table. The first label is never referenced, but tells ----
2611 // the assembler and linker the extents of the jump table object. The ----
2612 // second label is actually referenced by the code. ----
2613 if (JTInDiffSection && DL.hasLinkerPrivateGlobalPrefix()) 0
2614 // FIXME: This doesn't have to have any specific name, just any randomly ----
2615 // named and numbered local label started with 'l' would work. Simplify ----
2616 // GetJTISymbol. ----
2617 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetJTISymbol(JTI, true)); 0
2618 ----
2619 MCSymbol* JTISymbol = GetJTISymbol(JTI); 0
2620 OutStreamer->emitLabel(JTISymbol); 0
2621 ----
2622 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs) 0
2623 emitJumpTableEntry(MJTI, MBB, JTI); 0
2624 } ----
2625 if (!JTInDiffSection) 0
2626 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd); 0
2627 } ----
2628 ----
2629 /// EmitJumpTableEntry - Emit a jump table entry for the specified MBB to the ----
2630 /// current stream. ----
2631 void AsmPrinter::emitJumpTableEntry(const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI, 0
2632 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB, ----
2633 unsigned UID) const { ----
2634 assert(MBB && MBB->getNumber() >= 0 && "Invalid basic block"); 0
2635 const MCExpr *Value = nullptr; 0
2636 switch (MJTI->getEntryKind()) { 0
2637 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline: 0
2638 llvm_unreachable("Cannot emit EK_Inline jump table entry"); 0
2639 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Custom32: 0
2640 Value = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering()->LowerCustomJumpTableEntry( 0
2641 MJTI, MBB, UID, OutContext); ----
2642 break; 0
2643 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_BlockAddress: 0
2644 // EK_BlockAddress - Each entry is a plain address of block, e.g.: ----
2645 // .word LBB123 ----
2646 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
2647 break; 0
2648 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel32BlockAddress: { 0
2649 // EK_GPRel32BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded ----
2650 // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.: ----
2651 // .gprel32 LBB123 ----
2652 MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol(); 0
2653 OutStreamer->emitGPRel32Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext)); 0
2654 return; 0
2655 } ----
2656 ----
2657 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel64BlockAddress: { 0
2658 // EK_GPRel64BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded ----
2659 // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.: ----
2660 // .gpdword LBB123 ----
2661 MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol(); 0
2662 OutStreamer->emitGPRel64Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext)); 0
2663 return; 0
2664 } ----
2665 ----
2666 case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32: { 0
2667 // Each entry is the address of the block minus the address of the jump ----
2668 // table. This is used for PIC jump tables where gprel32 is not supported. ----
2669 // e.g.: ----
2670 // .word LBB123 - LJTI1_2 ----
2671 // If the .set directive avoids relocations, this is emitted as: ----
2672 // .set L4_5_set_123, LBB123 - LJTI1_2 ----
2673 // .word L4_5_set_123 ----
2674 if (MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) { 0
2675 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetJTSetSymbol(UID, MBB->getNumber()), 0
2676 OutContext); ----
2677 break; 0
2678 } ----
2679 Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
2680 const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering(); 0
2681 const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF, UID, OutContext); 0
2682 Value = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Value, Base, OutContext); 0
2683 break; 0
2684 } ----
2685 } ----
2686 ----
2687 assert(Value && "Unknown entry kind!"); 0
2688 ----
2689 unsigned EntrySize = MJTI->getEntrySize(getDataLayout()); 0
2690 OutStreamer->emitValue(Value, EntrySize); 0
2691 } ----
2692 ----
2693 /// EmitSpecialLLVMGlobal - Check to see if the specified global is a ----
2694 /// special global used by LLVM. If so, emit it and return true, otherwise ----
2695 /// do nothing and return false. ----
2696 bool AsmPrinter::emitSpecialLLVMGlobal(const GlobalVariable *GV) { 0
2697 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.used") { 0
2698 if (MAI->hasNoDeadStrip()) // No need to emit this at all. 0
2699 emitLLVMUsedList(cast(GV->getInitializer())); 0
2700 return true; 0
2701 } ----
2702 ----
2703 // Ignore debug and non-emitted data. This handles llvm.compiler.used. ----
2704 if (GV->getSection() == "llvm.metadata" || 0
2705 GV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage()) 0
2706 return true; 0
2707 ----
2708 if (!GV->hasAppendingLinkage()) return false; 0
2709 ----
2710 assert(GV->hasInitializer() && "Not a special LLVM global!"); 0
2711 ----
2712 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_ctors") { 0
2713 emitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(), 0
2714 /* isCtor */ true); ----
2715 ----
2716 return true; 0
2717 } ----
2718 ----
2719 if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_dtors") { 0
2720 emitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(), 0
2721 /* isCtor */ false); ----
2722 ----
2723 return true; 0
2724 } ----
2725 ----
2726 report_fatal_error("unknown special variable"); 0
2727 } ----

2729 /// EmitLLVMUsedList - For targets that define a MAI::UsedDirective, mark each ----
2730 /// global in the specified llvm.used list. ----
2731 void AsmPrinter::emitLLVMUsedList(const ConstantArray *InitList) { 0
2732 // Should be an array of 'i8*'. ----
2733 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InitList->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2734 const GlobalValue *GV = ----
2735 dyn_cast(InitList->getOperand(i)->stripPointerCasts()); 0
2736 if (GV) 0
2737 OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(GV), MCSA_NoDeadStrip); 0
2738 } ----

2740 ----
2741 void AsmPrinter::preprocessXXStructorList(const DataLayout &DL, 0
2742 const Constant *List, ----
2743 SmallVector &Structors) { ----
2744 // Should be an array of '{ i32, void ()*, i8* }' structs. The first value is ----
2745 // the init priority. ----
2746 if (!isa(List)) 0
2747 return; 0
2748 ----
2749 // Gather the structors in a form that's convenient for sorting by priority. ----
2750 for (Value *O : cast(List)->operands()) { 0
2751 auto *CS = cast(O); 0
2752 if (CS->getOperand(1)->isNullValue()) 0
2753 break; // Found a null terminator, skip the rest. 0
2754 ConstantInt *Priority = dyn_cast(CS->getOperand(0)); 0
2755 if (!Priority) 0
2756 continue; // Malformed. 0
2757 Structors.push_back(Structor()); 0
2758 Structor &S = Structors.back(); 0
2759 S.Priority = Priority->getLimitedValue(65535); 0
2760 S.Func = CS->getOperand(1); 0
2761 if (!CS->getOperand(2)->isNullValue()) { 0
2762 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSAIX()) 0
2763 llvm::report_fatal_error( 0
2764 "associated data of XXStructor list is not yet supported on AIX"); ----
2765 S.ComdatKey = 0
2766 dyn_cast(CS->getOperand(2)->stripPointerCasts()); 0
2767 } ----
2768 } ----
2769 ----
2770 // Emit the function pointers in the target-specific order ----
2771 llvm::stable_sort(Structors, [](const Structor &L, const Structor &R) { 0
2772 return L.Priority < R.Priority; 0
2773 }); ----
2774 } ----
2775 ----
2776 /// EmitXXStructorList - Emit the ctor or dtor list taking into account the init ----
2777 /// priority. ----
2778 void AsmPrinter::emitXXStructorList(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *List, 0
2779 bool IsCtor) { ----
2780 SmallVector Structors; 0
2781 preprocessXXStructorList(DL, List, Structors); 0
2782 if (Structors.empty()) 0
2783 return; 0
2784 ----
2785 // Emit the structors in reverse order if we are using the .ctor/.dtor ----
2786 // initialization scheme. ----
2787 if (!TM.Options.UseInitArray) 0
2788 std::reverse(Structors.begin(), Structors.end()); 0
2789 ----
2790 const Align Align = DL.getPointerPrefAlignment(); 0
2791 for (Structor &S : Structors) { 0
2792 const TargetLoweringObjectFile &Obj = getObjFileLowering(); 0
2793 const MCSymbol *KeySym = nullptr; 0
2794 if (GlobalValue *GV = S.ComdatKey) { 0
2795 if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker()) 0
2796 // If the associated variable is not defined in this module ----
2797 // (it might be available_externally, or have been an ----
2798 // available_externally definition that was dropped by the ----
2799 // EliminateAvailableExternally pass), some other TU ----
2800 // will provide its dynamic initializer. ----
2801 continue; 0
2802 ----
2803 KeySym = getSymbol(GV); 0
2804 } ----
2805 ----
2806 MCSection *OutputSection = ----
2807 (IsCtor ? Obj.getStaticCtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym) 0
2808 : Obj.getStaticDtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym)); 0
2809 OutStreamer->switchSection(OutputSection); 0
2810 if (OutStreamer->getCurrentSection() != OutStreamer->getPreviousSection()) 0
2811 emitAlignment(Align); 0
2812 emitXXStructor(DL, S.Func); 0
2813 } ----
2814 } 0

2950 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2951 // Constant emission. ----
2952 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2953 ----
2954 const MCExpr *AsmPrinter::lowerConstant(const Constant *CV) { 0
2955 MCContext &Ctx = OutContext; 0
2956 ----
2957 if (CV->isNullValue() || isa(CV)) 0
2958 return MCConstantExpr::create(0, Ctx); 0
2959 ----
2960 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
2961 return MCConstantExpr::create(CI->getZExtValue(), Ctx); 0
2962 ----
2963 if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
2964 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(GV), Ctx); 0
2965 ----
2966 if (const BlockAddress *BA = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
2967 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetBlockAddressSymbol(BA), Ctx); 0
2968 ----
2969 if (const auto *Equiv = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
2970 return getObjFileLowering().lowerDSOLocalEquivalent(Equiv, TM); 0
2971 ----
2972 if (const NoCFIValue *NC = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
2973 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(NC->getGlobalValue()), Ctx); 0
2974 ----
2975 const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(CV); 0
2976 if (!CE) { 0
2977 llvm_unreachable("Unknown constant value to lower!"); 0
2978 } ----
2979 ----
2980 // The constant expression opcodes are limited to those that are necessary ----
2981 // to represent relocations on supported targets. Expressions involving only ----
2982 // constant addresses are constant folded instead. ----
2983 switch (CE->getOpcode()) { 0
2984 default: 0
2985 break; // Error 0
2986 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: { 0
2987 const Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0); 0
2988 unsigned DstAS = CE->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
2989 unsigned SrcAS = Op->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace(); 0
2990 if (TM.isNoopAddrSpaceCast(SrcAS, DstAS)) 0
2991 return lowerConstant(Op); 0
2992 ----
2993 break; // Error 0
2994 } ----
2995 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: { 0
2996 // Generate a symbolic expression for the byte address ----
2997 APInt OffsetAI(getDataLayout().getPointerTypeSizeInBits(CE->getType()), 0); 0
2998 cast(CE)->accumulateConstantOffset(getDataLayout(), OffsetAI); 0
2999 ----
3000 const MCExpr *Base = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0)); 0
3001 if (!OffsetAI) 0
3002 return Base; 0
3003 ----
3004 int64_t Offset = OffsetAI.getSExtValue(); 0
3005 return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Base, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, Ctx), 0
3006 Ctx); 0
3007 } 0
3008 ----
3009 case Instruction::Trunc: 0
3010 // We emit the value and depend on the assembler to truncate the generated ----
3011 // expression properly. This is important for differences between ----
3012 // blockaddress labels. Since the two labels are in the same function, it ----
3013 // is reasonable to treat their delta as a 32-bit value. ----
3014 [[fallthrough]]; ----
3015 case Instruction::BitCast: ----
3016 return lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0)); 0
3017 ----
3018 case Instruction::IntToPtr: { 0
3019 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
3020 ----
3021 // Handle casts to pointers by changing them into casts to the appropriate ----
3022 // integer type. This promotes constant folding and simplifies this code. ----
3023 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0); 0
3024 Op = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Op, DL.getIntPtrType(CV->getType()), 0
3025 false/*ZExt*/); ----
3026 return lowerConstant(Op); 0
3027 } ----
3028 ----
3029 case Instruction::PtrToInt: { 0
3030 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
3031 ----
3032 // Support only foldable casts to/from pointers that can be eliminated by ----
3033 // changing the pointer to the appropriately sized integer type. ----
3034 Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0); 0
3035 Type *Ty = CE->getType(); 0
3036 ----
3037 const MCExpr *OpExpr = lowerConstant(Op); 0
3038 ----
3039 // We can emit the pointer value into this slot if the slot is an ----
3040 // integer slot equal to the size of the pointer. ----
3041 // ----
3042 // If the pointer is larger than the resultant integer, then ----
3043 // as with Trunc just depend on the assembler to truncate it. ----
3044 if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty).getFixedValue() <= 0
3045 DL.getTypeAllocSize(Op->getType()).getFixedValue()) 0
3046 return OpExpr; 0
3047 ----
3048 break; // Error 0
3049 } ----
3050 ----
3051 case Instruction::Sub: { 0
3052 GlobalValue *LHSGV; ----
3053 APInt LHSOffset; 0
3054 DSOLocalEquivalent *DSOEquiv; ----
3055 if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(0), LHSGV, LHSOffset, 0
3056 getDataLayout(), &DSOEquiv)) { ----
3057 GlobalValue *RHSGV; ----
3058 APInt RHSOffset; 0
3059 if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(1), RHSGV, RHSOffset, 0
3060 getDataLayout())) { ----
3061 const MCExpr *RelocExpr = ----
3062 getObjFileLowering().lowerRelativeReference(LHSGV, RHSGV, TM); 0
3063 if (!RelocExpr) { 0
3064 const MCExpr *LHSExpr = ----
3065 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(LHSGV), Ctx); 0
3066 if (DSOEquiv && 0
3067 getObjFileLowering().supportDSOLocalEquivalentLowering()) 0
3068 LHSExpr = ----
3069 getObjFileLowering().lowerDSOLocalEquivalent(DSOEquiv, TM); 0
3070 RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub( 0
3071 LHSExpr, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(RHSGV), Ctx), Ctx); 0
3072 } ----
3073 int64_t Addend = (LHSOffset - RHSOffset).getSExtValue(); 0
3074 if (Addend != 0) 0
3075 RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd( 0
3076 RelocExpr, MCConstantExpr::create(Addend, Ctx), Ctx); 0
3077 return RelocExpr; 0
3078 } ----
3079 } 0
3080 ----
3081 const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0)); 0
3082 const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(1)); 0
3083 return MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, RHS, Ctx); 0
3084 break; ----
3085 } 0
3086 ----
3087 case Instruction::Add: { 0
3088 const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0)); 0
3089 const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(1)); 0
3090 return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LHS, RHS, Ctx); 0
3091 } ----
3092 } ----
3093 ----
3094 // If the code isn't optimized, there may be outstanding folding ----
3095 // opportunities. Attempt to fold the expression using DataLayout as a ----
3096 // last resort before giving up. ----
3097 Constant *C = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, getDataLayout()); 0
3098 if (C != CE) 0
3099 return lowerConstant(C); 0
3100 ----
3101 // Otherwise report the problem to the user. ----
3102 std::string S; 0
3103 raw_string_ostream OS(S); 0
3104 OS << "Unsupported expression in static initializer: "; 0
3105 CE->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/false, 0
3106 !MF ? nullptr : MF->getFunction().getParent()); 0
3107 report_fatal_error(Twine(OS.str())); 0
3108 } ----

3111 AsmPrinter &AP, ----
3112 const Constant *BaseCV = nullptr, ----
3113 uint64_t Offset = 0, ----
3114 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList = nullptr); ----

3116 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(const ConstantFP *CFP, AsmPrinter &AP); ----
3117 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(APFloat APF, Type *ET, AsmPrinter &AP); ----

3119 /// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is ----
3120 /// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the ----
3121 /// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1. ----
3122 static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const ConstantDataSequential *V) { 0
3123 StringRef Data = V->getRawDataValues(); 0
3124 assert(!Data.empty() && "Empty aggregates should be CAZ node"); 0
3125 char C = Data[0]; 0
3126 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Data.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
3127 if (Data[i] != C) return -1; 0
3128 return static_cast(C); // Ensure 255 is not returned as -1. 0
3129 } ----
3130 ----
3131 /// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is ----
3132 /// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the ----
3133 /// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1. ----
3134 static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const Value *V, const DataLayout &DL) { 0
3135 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
3136 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(V->getType()); 0
3137 assert(Size % 8 == 0); 0
3138 ----
3139 // Extend the element to take zero padding into account. ----
3140 APInt Value = CI->getValue().zext(Size); 0
3141 if (!Value.isSplat(8)) 0
3142 return -1; 0
3143 ----
3144 return Value.zextOrTrunc(8).getZExtValue(); 0
3145 } 0
3146 if (const ConstantArray *CA = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
3147 // Make sure all array elements are sequences of the same repeated ----
3148 // byte. ----
3149 assert(CA->getNumOperands() != 0 && "Should be a CAZ"); 0
3150 Constant *Op0 = CA->getOperand(0); 0
3151 int Byte = isRepeatedByteSequence(Op0, DL); 0
3152 if (Byte == -1) 0
3153 return -1; 0
3154 ----
3155 // All array elements must be equal. ----
3156 for (unsigned i = 1, e = CA->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
3157 if (CA->getOperand(i) != Op0) 0
3158 return -1; 0
3159 return Byte; 0
3160 } ----
3161 ----
3162 if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast(V)) 0
3163 return isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS); 0
3164 ----
3165 return -1; 0
3166 } ----
3167 ----
3168 static void emitGlobalAliasInline(AsmPrinter &AP, uint64_t Offset, 0
3169 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3170 if (AliasList) { 0
3171 auto AliasIt = AliasList->find(Offset); 0
3172 if (AliasIt != AliasList->end()) { 0
3173 for (const GlobalAlias *GA : AliasIt->second) 0
3174 AP.OutStreamer->emitLabel(AP.getSymbol(GA)); 0
3175 AliasList->erase(Offset); 0
3176 } ----
3177 } ----
3178 } 0
3179 ----
3180 static void emitGlobalConstantDataSequential( 0
3181 const DataLayout &DL, const ConstantDataSequential *CDS, AsmPrinter &AP, ----
3182 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3183 // See if we can aggregate this into a .fill, if so, emit it as such. ----
3184 int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS, DL); 0
3185 if (Value != -1) { 0
3186 uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType()); 0
3187 // Don't emit a 1-byte object as a .fill. ----
3188 if (Bytes > 1) 0
3189 return AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value); 0
3190 } ----
3191 ----
3192 // If this can be emitted with .ascii/.asciz, emit it as such. ----
3193 if (CDS->isString()) 0
3194 return AP.OutStreamer->emitBytes(CDS->getAsString()); 0
3195 ----
3196 // Otherwise, emit the values in successive locations. ----
3197 unsigned ElementByteSize = CDS->getElementByteSize(); 0
3198 if (isa(CDS->getElementType())) { 0
3199 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CDS->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3200 emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, ElementByteSize * I, AliasList); 0
3201 if (AP.isVerbose()) 0
3202 AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS() 0
3203 << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n", CDS->getElementAsInteger(I)); 0
3204 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(CDS->getElementAsInteger(I), 0
3205 ElementByteSize); ----
3206 } ----
3207 } else { ----
3208 Type *ET = CDS->getElementType(); 0
3209 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CDS->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3210 emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, ElementByteSize * I, AliasList); 0
3211 emitGlobalConstantFP(CDS->getElementAsAPFloat(I), ET, AP); 0
3212 } ----
3213 } ----
3214 ----
3215 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType()); 0
3216 unsigned EmittedSize = ----
3217 DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getElementType()) * CDS->getNumElements(); 0
3218 assert(EmittedSize <= Size && "Size cannot be less than EmittedSize!"); 0
3219 if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize) 0
3220 AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Padding); 0
3221 } ----
3222 ----
3223 static void emitGlobalConstantArray(const DataLayout &DL, 0
3224 const ConstantArray *CA, AsmPrinter &AP, ----
3225 const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset, ----
3226 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3227 // See if we can aggregate some values. Make sure it can be ----
3228 // represented as a series of bytes of the constant value. ----
3229 int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CA, DL); 0
3230 ----
3231 if (Value != -1) { 0
3232 uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getType()); 0
3233 AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value); 0
3234 } else { ----
3235 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CA->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3236 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CA->getOperand(I), AP, BaseCV, Offset, 0
3237 AliasList); ----
3238 Offset += DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getOperand(I)->getType()); 0
3239 } ----
3240 } ----
3241 } 0
3242 ----
3243 static void emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(const ConstantInt *CI, AsmPrinter &AP); ----
3244 ----
3245 static void emitGlobalConstantVector(const DataLayout &DL, 0
3246 const ConstantVector *CV, AsmPrinter &AP, ----
3247 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3248 Type *ElementType = CV->getType()->getElementType(); 0
3249 uint64_t ElementSizeInBits = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElementType); 0
3250 uint64_t ElementAllocSizeInBits = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(ElementType); 0
3251 uint64_t EmittedSize; ----
3252 if (ElementSizeInBits != ElementAllocSizeInBits) { 0
3253 // If the allocation size of an element is different from the size in bits, ----
3254 // printing each element separately will insert incorrect padding. ----
3255 // ----
3256 // The general algorithm here is complicated; instead of writing it out ----
3257 // here, just use the existing code in ConstantFolding. ----
3258 Type *IntT = ----
3259 IntegerType::get(CV->getContext(), DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CV->getType())); 0
3260 ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast_or_null(ConstantFoldConstant( 0
3261 ConstantExpr::getBitCast(const_cast(CV), IntT), DL)); 0
3262 if (!CI) { 0
3263 report_fatal_error( 0
3264 "Cannot lower vector global with unusual element type"); ----
3265 } ----
3266 emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, 0, AliasList); 0
3267 emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(CI, AP); 0
3268 EmittedSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(CV->getType()); 0
3269 } else { ----
3270 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CV->getType()->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3271 emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()) * I, AliasList); 0
3272 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV->getOperand(I), AP); 0
3273 } ----
3274 EmittedSize = ----
3275 DL.getTypeAllocSize(ElementType) * CV->getType()->getNumElements(); 0
3276 } ----
3277 ----
3278 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()); 0
3279 if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize) 0
3280 AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Padding); 0
3281 } 0
3282 ----
3283 static void emitGlobalConstantStruct(const DataLayout &DL, 0
3284 const ConstantStruct *CS, AsmPrinter &AP, ----
3285 const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset, ----
3286 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3287 // Print the fields in successive locations. Pad to align if needed! ----
3288 unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CS->getType()); 0
3289 const StructLayout *Layout = DL.getStructLayout(CS->getType()); 0
3290 uint64_t SizeSoFar = 0; 0
3291 for (unsigned I = 0, E = CS->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
3292 const Constant *Field = CS->getOperand(I); 0
3293 ----
3294 // Print the actual field value. ----
3295 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, Field, AP, BaseCV, Offset + SizeSoFar, 0
3296 AliasList); ----
3297 ----
3298 // Check if padding is needed and insert one or more 0s. ----
3299 uint64_t FieldSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Field->getType()); 0
3300 uint64_t PadSize = ((I == E - 1 ? Size : Layout->getElementOffset(I + 1)) - 0
3301 Layout->getElementOffset(I)) - 0
3302 FieldSize; 0
3303 SizeSoFar += FieldSize + PadSize; 0
3304 ----
3305 // Insert padding - this may include padding to increase the size of the ----
3306 // current field up to the ABI size (if the struct is not packed) as well ----
3307 // as padding to ensure that the next field starts at the right offset. ----
3308 AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(PadSize); 0
3309 } ----
3310 assert(SizeSoFar == Layout->getSizeInBytes() && 0
3311 "Layout of constant struct may be incorrect!"); ----
3312 } 0
3313 ----
3314 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(APFloat APF, Type *ET, AsmPrinter &AP) { 0
3315 assert(ET && "Unknown float type"); 0
3316 APInt API = APF.bitcastToAPInt(); 0
3317 ----
3318 // First print a comment with what we think the original floating-point value ----
3319 // should have been. ----
3320 if (AP.isVerbose()) { 0
3321 SmallString<8> StrVal; 0
3322 APF.toString(StrVal); 0
3323 ET->print(AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS()); 0
3324 AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << ' ' << StrVal << '\n'; 0
3325 } 0
3326 ----
3327 // Now iterate through the APInt chunks, emitting them in endian-correct ----
3328 // order, possibly with a smaller chunk at beginning/end (e.g. for x87 80-bit ----
3329 // floats). ----
3330 unsigned NumBytes = API.getBitWidth() / 8; 0
3331 unsigned TrailingBytes = NumBytes % sizeof(uint64_t); 0
3332 const uint64_t *p = API.getRawData(); 0
3333 ----
3334 // PPC's long double has odd notions of endianness compared to how LLVM ----
3335 // handles it: p[0] goes first for *big* endian on PPC. ----
3336 if (AP.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() && !ET->isPPC_FP128Ty()) { 0
3337 int Chunk = API.getNumWords() - 1; 0
3338 ----
3339 if (TrailingBytes) 0
3340 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk--], TrailingBytes); 0
3341 ----
3342 for (; Chunk >= 0; --Chunk) 0
3343 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t)); 0
3344 } else { ----
3345 unsigned Chunk; ----
3346 for (Chunk = 0; Chunk < NumBytes / sizeof(uint64_t); ++Chunk) 0
3347 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t)); 0
3348 ----
3349 if (TrailingBytes) 0
3350 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], TrailingBytes); 0
3351 } ----
3352 ----
3353 // Emit the tail padding for the long double. ----
3354 const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout(); 0
3355 AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(DL.getTypeAllocSize(ET) - DL.getTypeStoreSize(ET)); 0
3356 } 0
3357 ----
3358 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(const ConstantFP *CFP, AsmPrinter &AP) { 0
3359 emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP->getValueAPF(), CFP->getType(), AP); 0
3360 } 0
3361 ----
3362 static void emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(const ConstantInt *CI, AsmPrinter &AP) { 0
3363 const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout(); 0
3364 unsigned BitWidth = CI->getBitWidth(); 0
3365 ----
3366 // Copy the value as we may massage the layout for constants whose bit width ----
3367 // is not a multiple of 64-bits. ----
3368 APInt Realigned(CI->getValue()); 0
3369 uint64_t ExtraBits = 0; 0
3370 unsigned ExtraBitsSize = BitWidth & 63; 0
3371 ----
3372 if (ExtraBitsSize) { 0
3373 // The bit width of the data is not a multiple of 64-bits. ----
3374 // The extra bits are expected to be at the end of the chunk of the memory. ----
3375 // Little endian: ----
3376 // * Nothing to be done, just record the extra bits to emit. ----
3377 // Big endian: ----
3378 // * Record the extra bits to emit. ----
3379 // * Realign the raw data to emit the chunks of 64-bits. ----
3380 if (DL.isBigEndian()) { 0
3381 // Basically the structure of the raw data is a chunk of 64-bits cells: ----
3382 // 0 1 BitWidth / 64 ----
3383 // [chunk1][chunk2] ... [chunkN]. ----
3384 // The most significant chunk is chunkN and it should be emitted first. ----
3385 // However, due to the alignment issue chunkN contains useless bits. ----
3386 // Realign the chunks so that they contain only useful information: ----
3387 // ExtraBits 0 1 (BitWidth / 64) - 1 ----
3388 // chu[nk1 chu][nk2 chu] ... [nkN-1 chunkN] ----
3389 ExtraBitsSize = alignTo(ExtraBitsSize, 8); 0
3390 ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[0] & 0
3391 (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize)); 0
3392 if (BitWidth >= 64) 0
3393 Realigned.lshrInPlace(ExtraBitsSize); 0
3394 } else ----
3395 ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[BitWidth / 64]; 0
3396 } ----
3397 ----
3398 // We don't expect assemblers to support integer data directives ----
3399 // for more than 64 bits, so we emit the data in at most 64-bit ----
3400 // quantities at a time. ----
3401 const uint64_t *RawData = Realigned.getRawData(); 0
3402 for (unsigned i = 0, e = BitWidth / 64; i != e; ++i) { 0
3403 uint64_t Val = DL.isBigEndian() ? RawData[e - i - 1] : RawData[i]; 0
3404 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(Val, 8); 0
3405 } ----
3406 ----
3407 if (ExtraBitsSize) { 0
3408 // Emit the extra bits after the 64-bits chunks. ----
3409 ----
3410 // Emit a directive that fills the expected size. ----
3411 uint64_t Size = AP.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(CI->getType()); 0
3412 Size -= (BitWidth / 64) * 8; 0
3413 assert(Size && Size * 8 >= ExtraBitsSize && 0
3414 (ExtraBits & (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize))) ----
3415 == ExtraBits && "Directive too small for extra bits."); ----
3416 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(ExtraBits, Size); 0
3417 } ----
3418 } 0
3419 ----
3420 /// Transform a not absolute MCExpr containing a reference to a GOT ----
3421 /// equivalent global, by a target specific GOT pc relative access to the ----
3422 /// final symbol. ----
3423 static void handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AsmPrinter &AP, const MCExpr **ME, 0
3424 const Constant *BaseCst, ----
3425 uint64_t Offset) { ----
3426 // The global @foo below illustrates a global that uses a got equivalent. ----
3427 // ----
3428 // @bar = global i32 42 ----
3429 // @gotequiv = private unnamed_addr constant i32* @bar ----
3430 // @foo = i32 trunc (i64 sub (i64 ptrtoint (i32** @gotequiv to i64), ----
3431 // i64 ptrtoint (i32* @foo to i64)) ----
3432 // to i32) ----
3433 // ----
3434 // The cstexpr in @foo is converted into the MCExpr `ME`, where we actually ----
3435 // check whether @foo is suitable to use a GOTPCREL. `ME` is usually in the ----
3436 // form: ----
3437 // ----
3438 // foo = cstexpr, where ----
3439 // cstexpr := - "." + ----
3440 // cstexpr := - ( - ) + ----
3441 // ----
3442 // After canonicalization by evaluateAsRelocatable `ME` turns into: ----
3443 // ----
3444 // cstexpr := - + gotpcrelcst, where ----
3445 // gotpcrelcst := + ----
3446 MCValue MV; 0
3447 if (!(*ME)->evaluateAsRelocatable(MV, nullptr, nullptr) || MV.isAbsolute()) 0
3448 return; 0
3449 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymA = MV.getSymA(); 0
3450 if (!SymA) 0
3451 return; 0
3452 ----
3453 // Check that GOT equivalent symbol is cached. ----
3454 const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = &SymA->getSymbol(); 0
3455 if (!AP.GlobalGOTEquivs.count(GOTEquivSym)) 0
3456 return; 0
3457 ----
3458 const GlobalValue *BaseGV = dyn_cast_or_null(BaseCst); 0
3459 if (!BaseGV) 0
3460 return; 0
3461 ----
3462 // Check for a valid base symbol ----
3463 const MCSymbol *BaseSym = AP.getSymbol(BaseGV); 0
3464 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymB = MV.getSymB(); 0
3465 ----
3466 if (!SymB || BaseSym != &SymB->getSymbol()) 0
3467 return; 0
3468 ----
3469 // Make sure to match: ----
3470 // ----
3471 // gotpcrelcst := + ----
3472 // ----
3473 // If gotpcrelcst is positive it means that we can safely fold the pc rel ----
3474 // displacement into the GOTPCREL. We can also can have an extra offset ----
3475 // if the target knows how to encode it. ----
3476 int64_t GOTPCRelCst = Offset + MV.getConstant(); 0
3477 if (GOTPCRelCst < 0) 0
3478 return; 0
3479 if (!AP.getObjFileLowering().supportGOTPCRelWithOffset() && GOTPCRelCst != 0) 0
3480 return; 0
3481 ----
3482 // Emit the GOT PC relative to replace the got equivalent global, i.e.: ----
3483 // ----
3484 // bar: ----
3485 // .long 42 ----
3486 // gotequiv: ----
3487 // .quad bar ----
3488 // foo: ----
3489 // .long gotequiv - "." + ----
3490 // ----
3491 // is replaced by the target specific equivalent to: ----
3492 // ----
3493 // bar: ----
3494 // .long 42 ----
3495 // foo: ----
3496 // .long bar@GOTPCREL+ ----
3497 AsmPrinter::GOTEquivUsePair Result = AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym]; 0
3498 const GlobalVariable *GV = Result.first; 0
3499 int NumUses = (int)Result.second; 0
3500 const GlobalValue *FinalGV = dyn_cast(GV->getOperand(0)); 0
3501 const MCSymbol *FinalSym = AP.getSymbol(FinalGV); 0
3502 *ME = AP.getObjFileLowering().getIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel( 0
3503 FinalGV, FinalSym, MV, Offset, AP.MMI, *AP.OutStreamer); 0
3504 ----
3505 // Update GOT equivalent usage information ----
3506 --NumUses; 0
3507 if (NumUses >= 0) 0
3508 AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(GV, NumUses); 0
3509 } ----
3510 ----
3511 static void emitGlobalConstantImpl(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV, 0
3512 AsmPrinter &AP, const Constant *BaseCV, ----
3513 uint64_t Offset, ----
3514 AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3515 emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, Offset, AliasList); 0
3516 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()); 0
3517 ----
3518 // Globals with sub-elements such as combinations of arrays and structs ----
3519 // are handled recursively by emitGlobalConstantImpl. Keep track of the ----
3520 // constant symbol base and the current position with BaseCV and Offset. ----
3521 if (!BaseCV && CV->hasOneUse()) 0
3522 BaseCV = dyn_cast(CV->user_back()); 0
3523 ----
3524 if (isa(CV) || isa(CV)) 0
3525 return AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Size); 0
3526 ----
3527 if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
3528 const uint64_t StoreSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(CV->getType()); 0
3529 ----
3530 if (StoreSize <= 8) { 0
3531 if (AP.isVerbose()) 0
3532 AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS() 0
3533 << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n", CI->getZExtValue()); 0
3534 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(CI->getZExtValue(), StoreSize); 0
3535 } else { ----
3536 emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(CI, AP); 0
3537 } ----
3538 ----
3539 // Emit tail padding if needed ----
3540 if (Size != StoreSize) 0
3541 AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Size - StoreSize); 0
3542 ----
3543 return; 0
3544 } ----
3545 ----
3546 if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
3547 return emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP, AP); 0
3548 ----
3549 if (isa(CV)) { 0
3550 AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, Size); 0
3551 return; 0
3552 } ----
3553 ----
3554 if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
3555 return emitGlobalConstantDataSequential(DL, CDS, AP, AliasList); 0
3556 ----
3557 if (const ConstantArray *CVA = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
3558 return emitGlobalConstantArray(DL, CVA, AP, BaseCV, Offset, AliasList); 0
3559 ----
3560 if (const ConstantStruct *CVS = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
3561 return emitGlobalConstantStruct(DL, CVS, AP, BaseCV, Offset, AliasList); 0
3562 ----
3563 if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast(CV)) { 0
3564 // Look through bitcasts, which might not be able to be MCExpr'ized (e.g. of ----
3565 // vectors). ----
3566 if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::BitCast) 0
3567 return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CE->getOperand(0), AP); 0
3568 ----
3569 if (Size > 8) { 0
3570 // If the constant expression's size is greater than 64-bits, then we have ----
3571 // to emit the value in chunks. Try to constant fold the value and emit it ----
3572 // that way. ----
3573 Constant *New = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, DL); 0
3574 if (New != CE) 0
3575 return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, New, AP); 0
3576 } ----
3577 } ----
3578 ----
3579 if (const ConstantVector *V = dyn_cast(CV)) 0
3580 return emitGlobalConstantVector(DL, V, AP, AliasList); 0
3581 ----
3582 // Otherwise, it must be a ConstantExpr. Lower it to an MCExpr, then emit it ----
3583 // thread the streamer with EmitValue. ----
3584 const MCExpr *ME = AP.lowerConstant(CV); 0
3585 ----
3586 // Since lowerConstant already folded and got rid of all IR pointer and ----
3587 // integer casts, detect GOT equivalent accesses by looking into the MCExpr ----
3588 // directly. ----
3589 if (AP.getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel()) 0
3590 handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AP, &ME, BaseCV, Offset); 0
3591 ----
3592 AP.OutStreamer->emitValue(ME, Size); 0
3593 } ----
3594 ----
3595 /// EmitGlobalConstant - Print a general LLVM constant to the .s file. ----
3596 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalConstant(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV, 0
3597 AliasMapTy *AliasList) { ----
3598 uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()); 0
3599 if (Size) 0
3600 emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV, *this, nullptr, 0, AliasList); 0
3601 else if (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) { 0
3602 // If the global has zero size, emit a single byte so that two labels don't ----
3603 // look like they are at the same location. ----
3604 OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, 1); 0
3605 } ----
3606 if (!AliasList) 0
3607 return; 0
3608 // TODO: These remaining aliases are not emitted in the correct location. Need ----
3609 // to handle the case where the alias offset doesn't refer to any sub-element. ----
3610 for (auto &AliasPair : *AliasList) { 0
3611 for (const GlobalAlias *GA : AliasPair.second) 0
3612 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getSymbol(GA)); 0
3613 } ----
3614 } ----

3768 /// emitBasicBlockStart - This method prints the label for the specified ----

3895 /// isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthough - Return true if the basic block has ----
3896 /// exactly one predecessor and the control transfer mechanism between ----
3897 /// the predecessor and this block is a fall-through. ----
3898 bool AsmPrinter:: 0
3899 isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const { ----
3900 // If this is a landing pad, it isn't a fall through. If it has no preds, ----
3901 // then nothing falls through to it. ----
3902 if (MBB->isEHPad() || MBB->pred_empty()) 0
3903 return false; 0
3904 ----
3905 // If there isn't exactly one predecessor, it can't be a fall through. ----
3906 if (MBB->pred_size() > 1) 0
3907 return false; 0
3908 ----
3909 // The predecessor has to be immediately before this block. ----
3910 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *MBB->pred_begin(); 0
3911 if (!Pred->isLayoutSuccessor(MBB)) 0
3912 return false; 0
3913 ----
3914 // If the block is completely empty, then it definitely does fall through. ----
3915 if (Pred->empty()) 0
3916 return true; 0
3917 ----
3918 // Check the terminators in the previous blocks ----
3919 for (const auto &MI : Pred->terminators()) { 0
3920 // If it is not a simple branch, we are in a table somewhere. ----
3921 if (!MI.isBranch() || MI.isIndirectBranch()) 0
3922 return false; 0
3923 ----
3924 // If we are the operands of one of the branches, this is not a fall ----
3925 // through. Note that targets with delay slots will usually bundle ----
3926 // terminators with the delay slot instruction. ----
3927 for (ConstMIBundleOperands OP(MI); OP.isValid(); ++OP) { 0
3928 if (OP->isJTI()) 0
3929 return false; 0
3930 if (OP->isMBB() && OP->getMBB() == MBB) 0
3931 return false; 0
3932 } ----
3933 } ----
3934 ----
3935 return true; 0
3936 } ----
